                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.4216L/74</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mayor of Warroad</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warroad, Minn.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Extreme high water in Lake of the Woods caused by dam at Kenora, Ontario, is
                    causing great damage to farmers on Minnesota side. A lot of land is washing away
                    and roads leading into Warroad are flooded. Kindly take action to give us
                    immediate relief.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Spreiter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
